Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.25,0:00:32.21,Signs,SIGN,0,0,0,,{\fad(1528,188)\blur0.25\fs33\fnGeorgia\fsp3.0\c&HF8CC9E&\t(2529,5824,\c&HFAFBFA&)\pos(326,245)}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.99,0:01:32.99,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0,0,0,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(394,269.5)}Episode 36: A Magnificent End
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.48,0:02:18.75,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,As I thought, this won't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.94,0:02:25.00,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,It's like fighting multiple \Nmaster swordsmen at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.76,0:02:27.78,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,On top of the sheer number of attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.78,0:02:31.00,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,his reflexes and stamina \Nfar exceed human levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.98,0:02:34.08,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,Stark is being overpowered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.08,0:02:37.99,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,If this becomes a battle \Nof endurance, we're sure to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.96,0:02:41.04,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,Should we retreat and regroup?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.96,0:02:46.42,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,No, he's faster than us. \NHe'd chase us down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.91,0:02:51.23,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0,0,0,,This is bad. Frieren was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:53.14,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0,0,0,,I can't read his attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.33,0:02:56.57,DefaultItalics,STARK/ID,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.12,0:03:04.12,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,Fool. I told him not to \Ntake his attacks head-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.59,0:03:05.63,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,You are mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.11,0:03:10.43,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,He let himself get cut on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.43,0:03:11.88,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,He's one tough kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.24,0:03:21.87,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Stark, you're a skilled warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.87,0:03:24.51,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,You created the slight opening I needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.04,0:03:36.11,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,It's over, Revolte.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.60,0:03:38.86,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,Wait. I remember now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:44.49,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,You're the partner of the \Nfirst-class mage I killed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.27,0:03:48.37,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,I recall the situation \Nwas similar to this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.37,0:03:54.25,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,You'd gone off to slay other demons, \Nwhile your partner defended the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:04:00.08,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,By the time you returned, it was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.48,0:04:03.58,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,Don't you want to know \Nhow your partner died?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.58,0:04:04.58,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:09.60,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,I learned a truly interesting \Nlesson from that battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.60,0:04:12.69,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Enough. I'll silence you myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.04,0:04:18.11,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,Then I have one last \Npiece of advice for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.54,0:04:22.83,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,You should check more \Nthoroughly for survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.38,0:04:25.43,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,A child?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:33.83,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,You're just delaying the inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.11,0:04:50.82,Default,JUNG,0,0,0,,I did it! I did it, Lord Revolte!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.82,0:04:51.65,Default,JUNG,0,0,0,,Praise—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.36,0:04:59.86,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,Well done. You have my thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.71,0:05:02.74,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,My judgment was clouded.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.08,0:05:05.84,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,For a moment, \Nall I could think of was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.24,0:05:10.56,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,I knew there couldn't be a child here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.67,0:05:19.13,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,I was right. Humans have a habit \Nof protecting their young.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.27,0:05:23.03,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.03,0:05:28.97,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,If that were true, the world \Nwould be a more peaceful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.56,0:05:36.13,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,I only ever knew one idiot who died \Nprotecting a child he didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.61,0:05:43.61,Flashback,SERIE,0,0,0,,Perhaps he was too kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.05,0:05:45.85,Flashback,SERIE,0,0,0,,It's the same in every era.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.71,0:05:49.62,Flashback,SERIE,0,0,0,,Kind mages don't live long.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.02,0:05:52.13,Flashback,GENAU,0,0,0,,He met a magnificent end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.95,0:05:57.36,Flashback,SERIE,0,0,0,,So even you say things you don't mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.97,0:06:00.99,Flashback,SERIE,0,0,0,,Genau, you're an unpleasant man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.44,0:06:03.29,Flashback,SERIE,0,0,0,,You don't have a shred of kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.30,0:06:10.04,Flashback,SERIE,0,0,0,,Stay that way forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.41,0:06:14.90,Flashback,GENAU,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.23,0:06:20.26,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,I do not enjoy killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.70,0:06:22.48,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,I shall put you out of your misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.42,0:06:28.23,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have acted out of character.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:38.75,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.28,0:06:45.80,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,I didn't think there was a warrior alive \Nwho could stop a direct hit from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.50,0:06:51.25,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,You can still move? \NYou should've played dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.75,0:06:53.91,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Then we would've lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.38,0:07:00.52,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Battles are won by whoever's \Nstill standing at the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.21,0:07:05.70,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,I thought you were a good person, \Nbut you're just an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.40,0:07:08.74,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,That's not a bad philosophy, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.24,0:07:14.83,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,I shall walk into the jaws \Nof death with you, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.18,0:07:20.59,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,The more desperate the battle, the more \Ncatharsis you feel when you survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.97,0:07:25.08,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to that. \NI can't stop shaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.99,0:07:40.14,DefaultItalics,FERN/ID,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.75,0:07:47.03,DefaultItalics,FERN/ID,0,0,0,,Ms. Frieren disappeared at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.66,0:07:55.80,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,It's nice to watch from afar \Nonce in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:12.67,Default,HEMMUNG,0,0,0,,It's pointless trying \Nto conceal your mana and hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.13,0:08:17.85,Default,HEMMUNG,0,0,0,,I created this fog with magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.85,0:08:21.77,Default,HEMMUNG,0,0,0,,It can detect and identify targets \Nfrom the faintest traces of mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.76,0:08:26.98,Default,HEMMUNG,0,0,0,,No living creature can \Nconceal their mana completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.86,0:08:39.45,DefaultItalics,FERN/ID,0,0,0,,Visibility is poor, \Nand he's blocking my attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.02,0:08:41.52,DefaultItalics,FERN/ID,0,0,0,,It's a bad matchup.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.83,0:09:01.72,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,I sense that Ms. Fern \Nis struggling as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.21,0:09:03.79,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,It's understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.79,0:09:07.48,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,Her opponent seems to be a demon \Nwho uses unconventional magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.76,0:09:08.98,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,Medrozobalt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.28,0:09:17.03,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,What are you looking at? \NI am your opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:18.74,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:32.82,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, my opponent is the\N opposite of "unconventional."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.82,0:09:36.09,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,Her combat style is tried-and-tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.09,0:09:39.84,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,Defending even while she attacks.\N Her fundamentals are solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.21,0:09:41.76,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,She simply has no openings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.66,0:09:46.18,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,I mustn't face her head-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.39,0:09:56.15,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,Ideally, I'd work with Ms. Fern \Nto bring both down,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.59,0:10:00.91,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,but this fog likely has powerful \Nmana-detection capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.52,0:10:06.37,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,Currently, Ms. Fern can't use stealth, \Nher greatest asset.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.37,0:10:12.38,DefaultItalics,METHODE/ID,0,0,0,,In which case, the situation would change \Ngreatly if this magic fog were removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.53,0:10:15.25,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Shall I cut loose a little?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:27.79,DefaultItalics,SOLIDE/ID,0,0,0,,A flurry of blows?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.79,0:10:29.65,DefaultItalics,SOLIDE/ID,0,0,0,,Her attack pattern changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.60,0:10:53.62,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,I recognize this fighting style.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:58.69,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,It's similar to one used by a clan that \Nhunted demons on the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.73,0:11:04.52,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,An insane clan that dedicated \Ntheir lives to killing demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:06.90,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,How interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.76,0:11:09.94,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,This should be a good match.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.04,0:11:13.15,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,Let's have a fair fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:24.57,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,He's fast. I can't land any of my spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:32.88,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,His masterful movements have become \Nthose of a savage predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:42.52,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,He's still fighting despite the \Nlife-threatening wounds he's suffered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.99,0:11:47.71,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,He has superhuman toughness \Nand inexhaustible stamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.02,0:11:51.68,DefaultItalics,GENAU/ID,0,0,0,,At this rate, he really will \Nkill us through attrition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.10,0:12:49.95,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Genau, his swords have weakened!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.95,0:12:51.32,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,We can break them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.32,0:12:57.46,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Indeed, he doesn't have the focus to \Nmaintain the mana in his swords anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.96,0:12:59.39,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Three to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:06.09,DefaultItalics,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.39,0:13:08.10,DefaultItalics,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,Why does something feel off?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.30,0:13:13.85,DefaultItalics,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,Her attacks are ferocious, \Nbut I sense no bloodlust.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.33,0:13:17.23,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Oh, you really are astute.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.27,0:13:21.86,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,But it took you too long to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:24.36,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,I've just finished analyzing the fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.28,0:13:32.62,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Those who only know how to fight \Nonly learn spells for combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.94,0:13:38.38,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Any other member of my clan probably \Nwouldn't have made it out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.04,0:13:43.25,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Because I doubt they'd \Nknow how fun magic is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.53,0:13:49.30,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Erilfrachte.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.59,0:13:58.40,DefaultItalics,HEMMUNG/ID,0,0,0,,The fog cleared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.98,0:14:00.39,DefaultItalics,HEMMUNG/ID,0,0,0,,How pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.54,0:14:04.01,DefaultItalics,HEMMUNG/ID,0,0,0,,I can simply create it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.01,0:14:11.19,Default,HEMMUNG,0,0,0,,Where did that girl go?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.91,0:14:24.97,DefaultItalics,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,Hemmung's mana vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.10,0:14:41.81,DefaultItalics,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,An attack? From where?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.27,0:14:56.54,Default,FERN,0,0,0,,Zoltraak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.97,0:15:02.30,Default,SOLIDE,0,0,0,,She's so far—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.05,0:15:15.53,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,A super-long-range attack from \Noutside their detection radius
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.53,0:15:17.23,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,whose trajectory can't be predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.01,0:15:20.60,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,Not bad, Fern. I'm impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.87,0:15:25.86,Default,FERN,0,0,0,,I'd rather not fight a battle \Nthis difficult again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.49,0:15:37.54,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Two to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.27,0:15:41.29,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.11,0:15:53.18,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,It's over, Revolte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.02,0:16:05.68,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,Only humans think empty hands \Ncan't be weapons on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.15,0:16:10.69,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,Your fatal assumption was that I wouldn't \Nbe able to fight if you disarmed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.22,0:16:13.00,Default,REVOLTE,0,0,0,,I win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.18,0:16:19.46,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our{\i0} fatal assumption? I think you'll find \Nboth humans and demons make those.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.94,0:16:23.07,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,For instance, you don't know \Nhow tenacious humans can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.85,0:16:37.59,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Cleaving Light!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.63,0:16:45.15,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Digardnacht.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.95,0:17:07.40,Flashback,STARK,0,0,0,,You seem like a good person to me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.61,0:17:12.14,Flashback,STARK,0,0,0,,You're still trying to defend the village,\Neven after it's been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.34,0:17:15.51,Flashback,STARK,0,0,0,,I couldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.76,0:17:32.73,Flashback,PARTNER,0,0,0,,You're still trying to save me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.40,0:17:39.07,Flashback,PARTNER,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.87,0:17:42.33,Flashback,PARTNER,0,0,0,,You're a good guy after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.89,0:18:17.45,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Methode.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.34,0:18:21.37,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Did I fail to die again?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.37,0:18:23.11,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,It would seem that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.71,0:18:25.73,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Enough. I can move again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.35,0:18:31.63,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,How is Stark?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:35.26,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,It was a close call, but he'll survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.48,0:18:40.75,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,I prioritized healing him over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.79,0:18:54.02,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.28,0:18:56.02,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Does that displease you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.02,0:18:59.78,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,No. He did well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.88,0:19:05.40,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Ms. Frieren's party will be staying \Nin the village for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:27.55,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Seems like I'm mostly better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.87,0:19:29.50,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,He's doing push-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.50,0:19:33.06,Default,FERN,0,0,0,,Could Mr. Stark possibly \Nbe a freak of nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:34.61,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,That's so mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.04,0:19:38.95,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,I noticed your party \Ndoesn't have a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.32,0:19:43.75,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,I'll be free for a while \Nonce this job is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.75,0:19:45.71,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Shall I accompany you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.04,0:19:50.82,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,The Northern Plateau is dangerous \Nwithout priest spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.20,0:19:52.77,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,We'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.77,0:19:56.33,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,I can't cast anything high-level \Nlike healing magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.33,0:19:59.38,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,but I know a few priest spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.40,0:20:03.86,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,If we find ourselves in serious trouble, \Nwe can always run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.86,0:20:05.72,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,That's what we've done until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.89,0:20:11.10,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,Besides, we want to keep \Nour priest slot open.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.68,0:20:15.26,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,We might see him again someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.00,0:20:17.16,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.03,0:20:21.49,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,For some reason, Fern seems \Nunhappy when you're around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.98,0:20:24.98,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Oh, my. I've made her hate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.38,0:20:28.77,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,But I also love you, Ms. Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.77,0:20:31.12,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,You're so cute when you're angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.09,0:20:33.00,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Methode.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.48,0:20:35.62,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,The Chivalric Order of Norm have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.99,0:20:39.97,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,We'll be accompanying \Nthem back to the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.75,0:20:42.34,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.86,0:20:45.43,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,This is where we say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.13,0:20:49.63,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Stark, how are your injuries?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.07,0:20:53.26,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,All good. No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:54.48,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.35,0:20:57.83,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,I owe you all a debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.83,0:20:59.72,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,One I intend to repay someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.28,0:21:01.42,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Mr. Genau.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.59,0:21:04.90,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,You're forgetting something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.04,0:21:10.41,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.38,0:21:13.11,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.11,0:21:14.91,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,I hope both of us live long lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.38,0:21:18.52,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.52,0:21:19.42,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.15,0:21:21.28,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.89,0:21:22.68,Default,GENAU,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.16,0:21:24.68,Default,METHODE,0,0,0,,May our paths cross again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.77,0:21:56.70,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Was it really the right move \Nto turn her down?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.46,0:22:00.15,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Methode, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.98,0:22:03.71,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,This party's priest is Sein.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.71,0:22:07.39,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,No, I mean she's a pretty older lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.39,0:22:10.22,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,Won't Sein complain \Nwhen we see him again?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.83,0:22:15.85,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,Who cares? This party \Nalready has an older lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.15,0:22:18.86,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,I guess that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.90,0:22:25.03,Credits,CREDITS,0,0,0,,{\fad(526,517)\fs10\pos(525,120)}Translation\N{\fs12}Sho Stifler\N\N{\fs10}Editing & Typesetting\N{\fs12}Geoff Mazzolini\N\N{\fs10}Subtitle Timing\N{\fs12}Edgar Cruz\N\N{\fs10}Quality Check\N{\fs12}Alicia Ashby\N\N{\fs10}Translation Check\N{\fs12}Elizabeth Ellis
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.10,0:23:51.81,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,It'll depend on the pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.68,0:23:54.24,DefaultOverlap,MAYOR,0,0,0,,Do dragons not normally travel in flights?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.38,0:23:53.02,DefaultTop,EISEN,0,0,0,,That's some terrible luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.05,0:23:54.45,Default,HIMMEL,0,0,0,,We're the party of heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.58,0:23:55.85,DefaultTop,HEITER,0,0,0,,I'm so bored, I could die.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.47,0:23:56.33,Default,STARK,0,0,0,,That's a tall order.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.00,0:23:57.63,DefaultOverlapTop,SAILOR,0,0,0,,I've looked up to him since I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.49,0:23:58.20,Default,FERN,0,0,0,,What's written in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.54,0:23:59.99,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0,0,0,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 37\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NHimmel's Memoirs
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.20,0:24:00.04,Default,FRIEREN,0,0,0,,Himmel's memoirs...